22/04/2004
TREBINJE, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The transport ministries of BiH, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro signed a joint statement Wednesday (21 April) on the Adriatic-Ionian Corridor project. Meeting in Trebinje, the ministers set forth the efforts each country will make towards promoting the project at the next Conference of European Ministers of Transport, to be held in Slovenia next month. The Adriatic-Ionian corridor is to connect Trieste, Italy to Kalamata, Greece via Slovenia, Croatia, Serbia-Montenegro, BiH and Albania. (HINA - 21/04/04)
